# Verdict — $exp_id

> The written verdict for this experiment: what was tried, what happened, and why.
> The AI writes the prose (Idea / Hypothesis / Verdict). The **numbers** (CV mean/std,
> fold scores, metric) are TOOLING-WRITTEN into `meta.json` / `result.json` by the
> recorder — the AI *references* them here, it never types a score by hand (D-05).

## Idea
_What was tried this cycle (one or two sentences)._

## Hypothesis
_The expected effect and why — the falsifiable claim this run tested._

## Result
_The CV score for this experiment is recorded by the tooling in_
`meta.json` _(`cv_mean ± cv_std`, per-fold scores) and_ `result.json`_. Reference
those numbers here in prose; do not hand-type them — a hand-typed number can drift
from the recorded one and poison the ledger._

## Verdict
_Did it work? Worked / Didn't / Inconclusive — and **why**. If it failed, name the
failure (the recorder sets `status="FAILED"` with a `failure_reason`); explain what
the failure teaches for the next hypothesis. A failure recorded with a clear verdict
is a successful cycle._
